fields: Who is our PE teacher?

A sequence of rhythmic steps or movements usually performed to music.
DANCE
What are the two main purposes of dance?
For pleasure or as a form of social interaction.
Enumerate the four elements of dance.
Body, Action, Space, Energy
The element of dance that refers to what others see; it can be still or in motion.
BODY
The element of dance that includes small movements like facial expressions or gestures, and larger movements like lifts or carries.
ACTION
The element of dance that refers to the space through which the dancer's body moves.
SPACE
The element of dance that helps us identify how the dancers move, such as with sharp and strong effort, or light and free.
ENERGY
A dance developed by the people on a certain place or region.
FOLK DANCE
An indigenous dance from a certain race or country.
ETHNIC DANCE
A type of dance that gives more attention to self-expression and individual creativity.
CONTEMPORARY DANCE
A set of partner dances, enjoyed both socially and competitively around the world.
BALLROOM DANCE
An organized sports activity involving short routines to cheer on teams.
CHEERDANCE
What three elements are combined in cheerdance?
Dance, gymnastics, and stunt elements
This dance style incorporates locking, popping, breakin, house and krumping.
HIPHOP
This dance style is described as very energetic, expressive, improvisational and social.
HIPHOP
This dance style's name comes from the fact that it originated on the streets and in clubs, not in dance studios.
STREET DANCE
Cultural dances performed to strong percussion beats in honor of a Patron Saint or in thanksgiving for a bountiful harvest.
FESTIVAL DANCE
Who is known as the Philippine National Artist and Mother of Philippine Folk Dances?
FRANCISCA REYES-AQUINO
Enumerate the eight natures of folk dance.
Occupational, Religious/Ceremonial, Comic, Game, Wedding, Courtship, Festival, War
A type of folk dance that depicts actions of a particular occupation.
OCCUPATIONAL DANCE
A type of folk dance associated with religion, vows, and ceremonies.
RELIGIOUS/CEREMONIAL DANCE
A type of folk dance that depicts funny movements for entertainment.
COMIC DANCE
A type of folk dance that is done with play elements.
GAME DANCE
A type of folk dance performed during weddings.
WEDDING DANCE
A type of folk dance that depicts the art of courtship.
COURTSHIP DANCE
A type of folk dance for festivity and suitable for special occasions.
FESTIVAL DANCE
A type of folk dance that shows imagery of combat.
WAR DANCE
Enumerate the five classifications of Philippine folk dance.
Maria Clara Dance, Cordillera Dance, Muslim Dance, Rural Dance, Tribal Dance
A classification of folk dance with Spanish influence, adopted from European dances.
MARIA CLARA DANCE
These dances originate from the Bontoc, Ifugao, Benguet, Apayo, & Kalinga tribes.
CORDILLERA DANCE
These dances reflect mysticism, royalty, and beauty.
MUSLIM DANCE
These dances reflect the simple life and perseverance of people in the barrio, depicting common work and daily activities.
RURAL DANCE
These dances are from T'boli, Bilaan, Manobo, and Bagobo.
TRIBAL DANCE
Tribal dance is also called what?
Lumad or Ethnic dances
